WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.920
(INSECTS CHIRP)
(WIND BLUSTERS)

00:03.920 --> 00:06.920
(FIRE CRACKLES)

00:06.920 --> 00:09.080
(OMINOUS MUSIC BUILDS)

00:09.080 --> 00:10.560
NEWSREADER: Fires across the country

00:10.560 --> 00:13.240
have burnt more than
6 million hectares...

00:13.240 --> 00:14.880
NEWSREADER 2: ..fires so volatile,

00:14.880 --> 00:16.920
they're creating
their own weather systems...

00:16.920 --> 00:18.480
MAN: ..just absolutely catastrophic,

00:18.480 --> 00:20.840
the flames dancing through
the tops of the trees...

00:20.840 --> 00:23.760
Smoke from the bushfires in Australia
has blown to New Zealand,

00:23.760 --> 00:26.600
blanketing some of the country's
retreating glaciers...

00:26.600 --> 00:28.480
(SIREN WAILS)

00:28.480 --> 00:30.840
NEWSREADER: ..emergency crews
were stretched thin,

00:30.840 --> 00:33.120
struggling in chaotic conditions.

00:33.120 --> 00:35.120
MAN 2: No-one can prepare you
for it. That's for sure.

00:43.360 --> 00:45.680
(WIND BLUSTERS)

00:50.880 --> 00:53.520
(DEEP WHOOSHING)

00:56.840 --> 00:59.280
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

01:01.200 --> 01:03.640
(RATTLING)

01:10.840 --> 01:12.640
(GENTLY) Hey...

01:12.640 --> 01:14.160
(WIND BLUSTERS)

01:16.760 --> 01:18.480
Ruth?

01:18.480 --> 01:20.000
Ruth?!

01:20.000 --> 01:21.640
(WOMAN IN DISTANCE) I'm here!

01:25.080 --> 01:27.120
Oh, shit. Shit!

01:29.600 --> 01:31.400
I can't get onto Leo!

01:31.400 --> 01:33.240
Maybe they got out!

01:33.240 --> 01:35.320
Call Hendo... Oh, Christ!

01:36.720 --> 01:38.320
Bastard!

01:38.320 --> 01:40.080
Ohh...

01:43.160 --> 01:46.360
Get the hose, quick!
Start wetting down!

01:47.360 --> 01:48.920
(GRUNTS)

01:52.200 --> 01:55.000
Ruth, I can't...I can't untangle it!

01:56.000 --> 01:57.880
Give it to me.
I'm doing my best!

01:59.720 --> 02:02.200
(FLAMES CRACKLING)

02:02.200 --> 02:03.800
Shit!

02:03.800 --> 02:05.280
Bucket. Go!

02:25.680 --> 02:28.680
(WIND CALMS)

02:28.680 --> 02:31.200
(BOTH BREATHE SHAKILY)

02:36.640 --> 02:39.320
Oh, yuck! Ash.

02:39.320 --> 02:41.480
I'm gonna try Leo and Maria again.

02:42.640 --> 02:44.120
Ohh...

02:45.360 --> 02:47.080
(LOUD CRACKLING)

02:47.080 --> 02:48.280
Fuck!

02:48.280 --> 02:50.440
It's hit their house!

02:50.440 --> 02:52.000
They would've gotten out.

02:52.000 --> 02:53.800
They would've gone.
They...they would've.

02:55.440 --> 02:57.200
(CREAKING AND CRACKLING)

03:01.200 --> 03:02.960
Oh, my God!

03:02.960 --> 03:04.400
No...

03:04.400 --> 03:05.720
(EXPLOSION BOOMS)

03:05.720 --> 03:08.360
Fuck! Oh!

03:08.360 --> 03:10.080
The animals!

03:13.520 --> 03:14.880
Nawra!

03:14.880 --> 03:17.320
Get the carry cages!
We'll get them to the ute!

03:17.320 --> 03:19.320
Take them to the sanctuary!

03:19.320 --> 03:20.640
Oh, shit!

03:23.440 --> 03:25.040
We can't drive in this.

03:25.040 --> 03:26.920
Nawra, we can't stay out here!

03:28.640 --> 03:30.680
Ruth, we can get them
in the house, OK?

03:30.680 --> 03:33.280
They're sick. It's our job
to look after them!

03:38.280 --> 03:41.320
(ROARING AND BLUSTERING)

03:41.320 --> 03:43.800
Go on, go. Hey, hey, come on.

03:43.800 --> 03:45.240
Go, go, go, go!

03:45.240 --> 03:47.200
Stop it! What are you doing?!

03:47.200 --> 03:49.480
Go on. Go, go, go!
They're gonna...they're gonna die!

03:49.480 --> 03:52.200
It's their best chance!
Ruth, we can get them in the house!

03:52.200 --> 03:55.400
There is no fucking time! Go!

03:55.400 --> 03:57.680
Nawra, go!

03:57.680 --> 04:00.680
(FIRE ROARS)

04:03.560 --> 04:05.480
(COUGHS)

04:06.760 --> 04:08.720
Shit. (PANTS)

04:10.600 --> 04:12.080
We could've gotten them out.

04:12.080 --> 04:13.840
We could've taken them
somewhere safe, Ruth.

04:13.840 --> 04:16.520
Call triple zero, you tell them
that we're in the house,

04:16.520 --> 04:19.760
we are sheltering in the laundry
and we are surrounded by fire.

04:19.760 --> 04:22.080
Tell them to get
the fire trucks here now.

04:23.840 --> 04:26.480
Hello? I can't hear you!
(RATTLING)

04:26.480 --> 04:28.720
Hey, come into the laundry.

04:30.040 --> 04:32.720
The fire is all around us!

04:32.720 --> 04:34.720
MAN: What's your location?

04:34.720 --> 04:37.520
10 Blue Wren Road, West Curran.

04:37.520 --> 04:39.040
Please just come quick.

04:39.040 --> 04:42.320
The fire service has no reports
of fires in that area.

04:44.560 --> 04:46.440
He's fucking joking, right?

04:46.440 --> 04:47.800
(BOOM!)

04:47.800 --> 04:50.320
(BOTH GRUNT AND PANT)

04:50.320 --> 04:52.400
Kip?
MAN: Yeah, coming.

04:52.400 --> 04:54.760
10 Blue Wren Road.

04:54.760 --> 04:56.160
(INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIOS)

04:56.160 --> 04:59.280
ESTA - two women sheltering,
West Curran.

05:00.280 --> 05:02.040
There's not supposed
to be a fire there.

05:04.720 --> 05:07.720
Curran sector commander
from Dumont ICC Operations.

05:07.720 --> 05:10.120
Good luck. I've been trying
to get him for 20 minutes.

05:14.520 --> 05:17.080
Dumont ICC to all sectors.

05:17.080 --> 05:19.560
Going to require a sitrep at 0500.

05:19.560 --> 05:21.520
MAN ON RADIO: Copy that.

05:24.440 --> 05:27.200
Greg, this just came in.

05:27.200 --> 05:29.200
Fire predictions are way off.

05:29.200 --> 05:30.760
I can't reach the sector commander

05:30.760 --> 05:33.560
and every appliance except the
strike team are at the Borriga fire.

05:35.640 --> 05:37.920
Get a sitrep from
the Queensland strike team leader

05:37.920 --> 05:39.400
and see if they can attend.

05:39.400 --> 05:40.560
Copy that.

05:41.560 --> 05:44.560
No way. I'm not leaving.
I'm defending my home.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.480
(MOTT SIGHS)

05:48.480 --> 05:50.880
That fire is 20 minutes away.

05:50.880 --> 05:53.960
We can't stay. And this place...

05:54.960 --> 05:56.440
It's not defendable.

05:56.440 --> 05:58.160
(PANTS)

05:58.160 --> 05:59.880
It's a tinderbox.

06:06.040 --> 06:08.040
Have you got anywhere safe to go?

06:08.040 --> 06:09.840
You tell us. Where's safe?

06:09.840 --> 06:13.800
Rollo's opened up the co-op.
I saw it online.

06:13.800 --> 06:16.040
Tash! Priority call.

06:18.840 --> 06:20.880
10 Blue Wren Road, West Curran.

06:20.880 --> 06:22.680
Two women sheltering - priority.

06:22.680 --> 06:25.160
Acknowledged - priority,
10 Blue Wren Road, West Curran.

06:25.160 --> 06:27.160
Wilco. Over. Mott, we've gotta go.

06:28.160 --> 06:30.080
That is so close.

06:30.080 --> 06:32.560
Just head back to town.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.040
Please.

06:37.160 --> 06:39.920
(FIRE TRUCK ENGINE STARTS)

06:41.160 --> 06:43.440
(NAWRA COUGHS)
The ute's OK for now.

06:43.440 --> 06:46.520
But if the fire gets to it...
(IMITATES EXPLOSION)

06:46.520 --> 06:49.440
What do we do?
We wait for the firies.

06:49.440 --> 06:51.440
(NAWRA COUGHS)

06:51.440 --> 06:53.440
It's OK. The concrete's
gonna keep us cool.

06:53.440 --> 06:55.440
And if it gets really bad,

06:55.440 --> 06:57.760
we cover ourselves
and we wait for it to burn over.

06:58.760 --> 07:01.040
(CRACKING AND BLUSTERING OUTSIDE)

07:01.040 --> 07:03.960
(BREATHES SHALLOWLY)

07:03.960 --> 07:07.240
We need to get low. Come on.
(COUGHS)

07:10.720 --> 07:13.880
(BOTH BREATHE HEAVILY)

07:16.480 --> 07:19.520
(BOOMING AND RATTLING OUTSIDE)

07:25.240 --> 07:27.120
Don't. Don't do that to me now.

07:28.240 --> 07:29.840
Yeah.

07:29.840 --> 07:31.440
(COUGHS)

07:33.600 --> 07:36.800
We'll be OK. It's OK.

07:39.360 --> 07:42.040
(BUILDING RATTLES)

07:46.600 --> 07:49.200
(FIRE WHOOSHING
AND CRACKLING OUTSIDE)

07:52.800 --> 07:54.600
(NAWRA COUGHS)

07:59.880 --> 08:02.920
(CRACKLING)

08:02.920 --> 08:04.520
WOMAN: There's still
20-something residents

08:04.520 --> 08:06.040
at the Valla Nursing Home.

08:06.040 --> 08:08.720
Caller said they could
see flames approaching!

08:08.720 --> 08:11.320
Have you been able to get onto
the section commander for that area?

08:11.320 --> 08:13.560
Still not responding.
They're flat out on the fire ground.

08:13.560 --> 08:15.440
OK, well, who else is close by?

08:15.440 --> 08:17.320
What about Weimar?
On their way to Borriga.

08:17.320 --> 08:20.040
Too far. I got no-one!
No-one I can raise anyway.

08:20.040 --> 08:22.040
They're all off the radios.

08:22.040 --> 08:24.480
GREG: It's north-east of Curran.

08:25.720 --> 08:29.000
No...no! No way, mate. No way!

08:29.000 --> 08:30.760
Queensland team's the closest.

08:30.760 --> 08:33.760
What about my women on Blue Wren?
Nursing home's a priority call.

08:33.760 --> 08:35.920
Blue Wren's a priority call, Dell.
There's two people.

08:35.920 --> 08:39.680
Valla's 20, more, old folk,
and they can't be moved.

08:39.680 --> 08:41.320
Mate, the...

08:42.320 --> 08:43.480
Please.

08:44.640 --> 08:46.720
Reroute the Queensland team.

08:51.480 --> 08:53.240
(CLEARS THROAT)

08:56.600 --> 09:00.000
Strike Team QFB 04
from Dumont ICC Operations.

09:00.000 --> 09:01.520
I've got a priority call.

09:01.520 --> 09:03.960
Around 20 people
sheltering at Valla Nursing Home.

09:03.960 --> 09:06.480
(WINCES)
MOTT: Copy that. Rerouting now.

09:06.480 --> 09:08.840
What about Blue Wren priority job?

09:08.840 --> 09:10.440
KIP ON RADIO: I'll let them know.

09:10.440 --> 09:12.360
(SIREN WAILS)

09:12.360 --> 09:13.840
Who's going to those women?

09:16.560 --> 09:18.200
I'm calling in medical for you.

09:18.200 --> 09:19.720
No, I'll be fine.

09:21.960 --> 09:25.800
Dumont ICC Operations
from Strike Team QFB 04.

09:25.800 --> 09:27.640
We have an injured team member.

09:27.640 --> 09:29.240
Can we organise a pick-up for him

09:29.240 --> 09:31.560
to be transported
for medical assistance?

09:31.560 --> 09:33.960
(INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIOS)

09:38.160 --> 09:40.320
Kip Fisher from Vic Forests.
Are you safe to talk?

09:40.320 --> 09:43.320
RUTH: Where are the trucks?
The roof is on fire!

09:43.320 --> 09:45.320
OK, you need to find shelter.

09:45.320 --> 09:47.400
Is there a safe place
you can get to?

09:47.400 --> 09:50.200
There is no safe place.
The whole house is burning!

09:50.200 --> 09:52.040
KIP: Listen,
you need woollen blankets,

09:52.040 --> 09:53.520
dry, not wet.

09:53.520 --> 09:55.000
You need to get underneath them.

09:55.000 --> 09:58.840
We've got blankets.
What we need is trucks!

09:58.840 --> 10:01.360
You need to keep calm and stay low.

10:01.360 --> 10:03.120
When will they get here?!

10:04.120 --> 10:05.760
I'm sorry, but we currently have

10:05.760 --> 10:08.400
no available appliances
in responding distance.

10:08.400 --> 10:11.520
(WHOOSHING OUTSIDE)

10:11.520 --> 10:13.400
No, they...they...

10:13.400 --> 10:16.600
Um, they said that
a truck was coming.

10:16.600 --> 10:18.240
(CLEARS THROAT)

10:18.240 --> 10:21.160
We are unable to respond
to your call at this time.

10:21.160 --> 10:24.480
If, uh, an appliance
does become available, we will...

10:24.480 --> 10:26.960
Oh, FUCK!

10:26.960 --> 10:30.760
(NAWRA COUGHS AND WHEEZES)

10:31.760 --> 10:33.600
(WEEPS)

10:33.600 --> 10:35.760
We're on our own.

10:38.680 --> 10:41.160
(BOTH COUGH)

10:44.960 --> 10:47.200
(GASPS) OK.
(WEEPS)

10:48.200 --> 10:49.960
OK, come on.

10:49.960 --> 10:51.560
Come on. Crying's not gonna help.

10:51.560 --> 10:54.080
(SOBS)
Hey, listen.

10:54.080 --> 10:55.560
Hey.

10:57.480 --> 11:00.600
The ute...
I don't think I... I can't.

11:00.600 --> 11:03.480
I don't think I can do it.
I can't do it.

11:04.800 --> 11:06.720
Hey.

11:06.720 --> 11:10.440
It's 100 metres
and we can make it, mm?

11:10.440 --> 11:14.360
No, it's...it's too late
to leave. That's what you said.

11:14.360 --> 11:17.800
(WEEPS) And what...what about the...

11:17.800 --> 11:19.280
Oh!

11:20.760 --> 11:22.680
I'm not dying in here.

11:26.640 --> 11:29.560
Oh... (WEEPS)

11:31.160 --> 11:33.440
You don't stop for anything.

11:34.560 --> 11:35.680
Go!

11:35.680 --> 11:38.200
(BOTH PANT AND COUGH)

11:45.120 --> 11:47.200
Oh, fuck!
(FIRE ROARS)

11:51.280 --> 11:53.720
(COUGHS)
Holy fuck.

12:00.000 --> 12:01.640
(BOTH COUGH AND WHEEZE)

12:06.680 --> 12:08.880
(BOTH COUGH)

12:12.920 --> 12:15.320
(TREES CRACK)

12:17.280 --> 12:19.080
Oh, my God!

12:19.080 --> 12:21.640
(ENGINE SPUTTERS)
Oh, God!

12:21.640 --> 12:24.080
Oh, my God. Come on! Let's go!

12:24.080 --> 12:26.440
Go! Go! Go!

12:26.440 --> 12:29.480
(TENSE MUSIC)

12:35.640 --> 12:38.640
(WOMEN BREATHE HEAVILY)

12:53.360 --> 12:55.120
(COUGHS)

12:56.200 --> 12:59.080
(CRACKLING AND WHOOSHING
IN DISTANCE)

13:14.120 --> 13:15.680
We made it!

13:16.880 --> 13:20.120
We did it, Ruth. You got us out.

13:20.120 --> 13:22.280
Hey, let's go to town.

13:23.520 --> 13:25.320
Find somewhere safe.

13:27.360 --> 13:28.840
Ruth?

13:40.400 --> 13:42.080
You do whatever you want.

13:43.360 --> 13:45.080
I don't care.

13:49.000 --> 13:50.560
(VEHICLE DOOR OPENS)

13:50.560 --> 13:51.960
(COUGHS)

13:52.960 --> 13:54.120
(DOOR SHUTS)

13:54.120 --> 13:57.120
(SOMBRE MUSIC)

14:34.240 --> 14:37.240
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

14:42.080 --> 14:43.960
(NAWRA COUGHS)

14:43.960 --> 14:46.480
(INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIO)

14:52.360 --> 14:55.880
(CHATTER CONTINUES OVER RADIO)

14:55.880 --> 14:58.480
WOMAN: What happened?
NAWRA: We got out.

14:58.480 --> 15:00.840
Oh, shit! Hey, you right?

15:00.840 --> 15:03.040
RUTH: Yeah, we're right.

15:03.040 --> 15:04.600
(SNIFFLES)

15:06.880 --> 15:08.720
Your place?

15:09.760 --> 15:11.360
Yeah, yeah.

15:12.600 --> 15:15.840
So West Curran's gone up now?
Jesus Christ!

15:17.600 --> 15:19.200
We need to get out of here.

15:19.200 --> 15:21.040
We need to get down
to the coast, yeah?

15:21.040 --> 15:22.600
They've been up all night.

15:26.160 --> 15:29.200
I couldn't get onto Leo and Maria.

15:31.320 --> 15:32.920
Grab the ladies
some water, would you?

15:32.920 --> 15:35.320
Back kitchenette,
cups above the sink.

15:35.320 --> 15:36.640
Give us a hand, babe.

15:36.640 --> 15:38.360
For God's sake, take a load off.

15:41.880 --> 15:43.680
Where's your family? They alright?

15:43.680 --> 15:45.800
Uh, the evacuation centre
down the coast.

15:45.800 --> 15:47.640
I sent them there
a couple of days ago.

15:47.640 --> 15:49.840
Where was our warning?
Ruth...

15:49.840 --> 15:51.600
No, you're on the council,
Rollo! If you...

15:51.600 --> 15:54.560
It doesn't give me
a direct line to God, Ruth.

15:54.560 --> 15:57.120
MAN: Hey, here you go, mate. Here.

15:57.120 --> 15:58.800
WOMAN: Hey.
Thanks.

15:58.800 --> 16:00.920
(INDISTINCT CHATTER ON RADIO)

16:00.920 --> 16:03.280
MAN ON RADIO: It's too intense.
We're pulling back.

16:03.280 --> 16:05.280
(CHATTER CONTINUES)

16:05.280 --> 16:07.360
Did you get the rest
of your critters out, hon?

16:08.640 --> 16:11.600
We were in the middle
of rehoming them when it hit.

16:13.920 --> 16:15.560
Aww...

16:15.560 --> 16:17.120
Poor little fella.

16:17.120 --> 16:20.160
Yeah, we had to let
the rest of them go.

16:20.160 --> 16:22.200
Some of them were just babies.

16:23.240 --> 16:25.280
Did you have a good
Chrissie at least?

16:25.280 --> 16:27.560
Did we have a good Chrissie, Ruth?

16:28.560 --> 16:30.400
Don't, Nawra.

16:32.480 --> 16:34.120
Sorry. Did I say something?

16:34.120 --> 16:35.800
No, no.

16:36.800 --> 16:38.360
Sorry. We broke up.

16:39.360 --> 16:41.280
Far out.

16:41.280 --> 16:42.960
(SIGHS) Timing.

16:42.960 --> 16:44.840
Yeah.

16:44.840 --> 16:47.920
(DELL SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY)
Borriga Pumper, please report.

16:47.920 --> 16:50.040
Do you have a sitrep...
Hey, Greg?

16:50.040 --> 16:52.680
Um, Blue Wren Road, mate,
did you get anyone in?

16:52.680 --> 16:55.560
The council tried.
They got pushed back.

16:55.560 --> 16:57.680
Nobody can get through.

16:57.680 --> 16:59.680
Queensland could have got there.

16:59.680 --> 17:01.200
DELL: Copy that, Kuara.

17:02.240 --> 17:03.400
Please report.

17:03.400 --> 17:07.040
TASH ON RADIO: Dumont ICC
Operations from Strike Team QFB 04.

17:07.040 --> 17:08.520
Come in, Queensland.

17:08.520 --> 17:11.200
Uh, we've assessed the nursing home.

17:11.200 --> 17:13.280
There's good clearance all around.
No immediate threat.

17:13.280 --> 17:16.320
We advise they stay in and just
call in again if there's a threat.

17:16.320 --> 17:19.800
DELL ON RADIO: We had
a report of visible flames.

17:19.800 --> 17:21.920
I think they just got spooked.

17:21.920 --> 17:23.840
Wait. Valla was a bust?

17:23.840 --> 17:25.960
TASH: Also,
reporting the team member

17:25.960 --> 17:28.080
has been picked up
by medical support unit.

17:28.080 --> 17:29.840
Copy that.

17:29.840 --> 17:31.760
You can head
to Curran town and refuel.

17:31.760 --> 17:33.320
(KIP SIGHS)

17:39.200 --> 17:41.920
The caller said
they could see the fire.

17:41.920 --> 17:43.640
They were really distressed.

17:43.640 --> 17:45.840
We couldn't get reports
from the ground so we had to...

17:45.840 --> 17:47.840
That team should've been
sent to Blue Wren Road

17:47.840 --> 17:49.360
when it still had a chance
to get in there.

17:49.360 --> 17:50.640
We can't second-guess, Kip!

17:50.640 --> 17:52.040
Well, now it's too late, isn't it,

17:52.040 --> 17:53.520
because someone saw smoke
and freaked out.

17:53.520 --> 17:55.240
We can only go on
the information we're given.

17:55.240 --> 17:57.240
They said there were flames!
You need a break?

17:57.240 --> 17:58.640
No, mate, I don't need a break.

17:58.640 --> 17:59.840
I need a fucking truck

17:59.840 --> 18:01.640
when I've got two people
trapped in a burning house.

18:01.640 --> 18:04.080
I can't pull trucks I don't have!
Well, we had one, Dell!

18:04.080 --> 18:06.840
We had one.
You took it for a false alarm.

18:11.480 --> 18:13.640
Borriga Pumper 2, please report.

18:13.640 --> 18:15.120
(SQUEAKS)

18:15.120 --> 18:17.440
KIP ON RADIO: Borriga Pumper 2,
loop back.

18:17.440 --> 18:20.040
(KIP CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)

18:20.040 --> 18:22.080
Can we find out
if the coast road's clear yet?

18:23.080 --> 18:26.640
It's not a bloody two-way,
Macca. It's a scanner.

18:26.640 --> 18:28.160
We need to get the kids out.

18:33.200 --> 18:35.320
Huh, it's just gobbledegook.

18:35.320 --> 18:37.080
MACCA: Where are you gonna go?

18:38.360 --> 18:40.200
Gonna wait here
till it's safe to go back.

18:40.200 --> 18:43.480
Oh, for Godsakes,
there's nothing left!

18:43.480 --> 18:47.320
And I need to check on Leo and Maria.

18:52.880 --> 18:54.800
What size boots do you take?

18:54.800 --> 18:57.600
I don't know. Uh, nine or...

19:01.840 --> 19:03.880
(SIGHS)
RADIO: Request backup at Borriga.

19:03.880 --> 19:06.480
What's our local crew
doing in Borriga?

19:06.480 --> 19:09.160
It's all I've got in your size,
but you know what?

19:09.160 --> 19:10.920
I think they've got
your name on them.

19:11.960 --> 19:13.000
Thanks.

19:13.000 --> 19:16.440
Why aren't our crews here?
What are they doing 50 k's away?

19:16.440 --> 19:18.280
We had frigging Queenslanders
come to ours.

19:18.280 --> 19:20.640
All our crews got pulled.

19:20.640 --> 19:23.680
There's something like a hundred
houses under threat up there.

19:23.680 --> 19:25.240
My house was under threat!

19:25.240 --> 19:28.000
They were heading to Blue Wren,
those Queenslanders.

19:28.000 --> 19:29.480
I heard 'em.

19:30.680 --> 19:33.200
Yeah, they...they said
someone was coming

19:33.200 --> 19:34.920
and then they called back and they...

19:38.200 --> 19:40.280
They fuckin' abandoned us.

19:40.280 --> 19:42.440
ROLLO: They're doing
the best they can.

19:42.440 --> 19:45.040
Nobody knew it was
going to get this bad.

19:45.040 --> 19:46.240
They bloody knew.

19:46.240 --> 19:48.600
The government had plenty of warning
that this summer was coming.

19:48.600 --> 19:50.400
It's the government's
fault again, right?

19:50.400 --> 19:53.520
If they had even bothered to meet
with that group of fire chiefs,

19:53.520 --> 19:55.080
they could've been properly prepared.

19:55.080 --> 19:58.280
Piss off, Ruth. You're not
the only one who's hurting here.

19:58.280 --> 19:59.880
My place went up last night too

19:59.880 --> 20:02.680
and I haven't been able to get out
there to see what's still standing

20:02.680 --> 20:05.160
because I'm stuck here with you lot.

20:11.040 --> 20:13.080
Why didn't you say anything?

20:13.080 --> 20:14.560
What for?

20:14.560 --> 20:16.320
You gonna get me a hankie?

20:19.280 --> 20:22.240
(INDISTINCT CHATTER OVER RADIO)

20:24.080 --> 20:25.760
What was that?

20:25.760 --> 20:27.360
The grid's down again.

20:27.360 --> 20:29.760
I'll get the genny going.

20:35.520 --> 20:37.000
(TENSE MUSIC)

20:37.000 --> 20:39.080
Oh, my God!

20:39.080 --> 20:41.840
Ruth, look.

20:45.160 --> 20:46.320
Maria!

20:48.720 --> 20:50.200
Oh...

20:54.640 --> 20:56.440
(EXHALES HEAVILY)

20:59.000 --> 21:01.040
It's all gone.

21:02.960 --> 21:04.680
Where's Leo?

21:04.680 --> 21:06.760
He went out the back
to check on the cows.

21:07.760 --> 21:11.760
The fire just came tearing through
and Leo wasn't back with the ute

21:11.760 --> 21:14.720
so I just put on my boots
and ran out.

21:16.000 --> 21:18.960
(TREMBLES AND WEEPS)

21:24.840 --> 21:27.200
Now, you need something? You hungry?

21:27.200 --> 21:29.280
NAWRA: Cup of tea?

21:29.280 --> 21:30.360
Yeah.

21:31.440 --> 21:33.760
Milk and two sugars,
and leave the bag in.

21:36.880 --> 21:38.800
I shouldn't have left him, Ruth.

21:38.800 --> 21:40.680
I should've stayed.

21:42.320 --> 21:45.440
(WIND BLUSTERS, TIN RATTLES)

21:51.640 --> 21:53.280
Hang on.

21:53.280 --> 21:54.760
(WOMAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ON RADIO)

21:54.760 --> 21:56.760
MAN ON RADIO: We need backup...

21:56.760 --> 22:01.400
Now, this little fella
really likes to be close to someone.

22:01.400 --> 22:02.840
Here you go.

22:02.840 --> 22:04.560
Oh!

22:04.560 --> 22:06.240
Hey?

22:07.400 --> 22:10.280
He's a real snuggle-pie. (SNIFFS)
(TALKS SOFTLY)

22:10.280 --> 22:12.040
Hey, big sook.
Hello, beautiful.

22:12.040 --> 22:14.280
(KISSES)
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

22:15.560 --> 22:17.440
(MARIA MURMURS GENTLY)

22:17.440 --> 22:19.240
You're safe, young one.

22:22.240 --> 22:25.800
(RATTLING, WIND BLUSTERS)

22:41.320 --> 22:43.960
I don't have to go straightaway.

22:45.400 --> 22:48.120
I mean, you'll need
to rebuild the cages,

22:48.120 --> 22:50.080
all the injured wildlife...

22:50.080 --> 22:52.160
The shelter won't be able
to cope with them all.

22:53.200 --> 22:54.360
No, thanks.

22:55.360 --> 22:57.120
It's a massive job.

22:57.120 --> 22:59.560
And the house...

22:59.560 --> 23:01.280
You hate paperwork.

23:02.280 --> 23:03.760
I can cope.

23:04.920 --> 23:06.240
Ruth...

23:07.440 --> 23:10.080
I don't want you hanging around here
'cause you feel sorry for me.

23:10.080 --> 23:12.680
No, that's not it!
No? It's what it sounds like.

23:12.680 --> 23:15.080
Why do you have to do that?

23:20.160 --> 23:23.360
That first night we were together,

23:23.360 --> 23:25.160
do you remember what you said?

23:26.160 --> 23:28.960
You said, "This isn't gonna last."

23:31.840 --> 23:33.920
Well, I was right, wasn't I?

23:35.560 --> 23:37.040
You want to leave.

23:37.040 --> 23:38.920
Because you have never given me

23:38.920 --> 23:41.320
even the slightest hint
you'd care if I stayed.

23:43.880 --> 23:47.080
MARIA: Sorry. Look,
I don't mean to be a stickybeak.

23:47.080 --> 23:48.840
But he's just wet.

23:48.840 --> 23:51.400
I'll get something. Here.

24:03.080 --> 24:05.560
Don't.
What?

24:05.560 --> 24:07.240
Push her away.

24:07.240 --> 24:08.880
She's leaving me!

24:08.880 --> 24:11.200
She's leaving
because you're impossible!

24:11.200 --> 24:14.880
Everybody around here loves you,
Ruthie, but you don't make it easy.

24:14.880 --> 24:16.840
So you're on her side too?

24:28.720 --> 24:31.160
Hey, take a break.

24:31.160 --> 24:33.160
Go on. Take a break.

24:33.160 --> 24:34.720
I got it.

24:37.480 --> 24:40.480
Last stop and then we're home free.

24:40.480 --> 24:42.320
Yeah, for five days.

24:43.680 --> 24:46.000
I'm gonna sleep for half of 'em.

24:46.000 --> 24:49.120
(LAUGHS) You better be awake
for New Year's

24:49.120 --> 24:50.640
'cause we're going dancing.

24:50.640 --> 24:52.680
Mmm...

24:59.120 --> 25:00.440
(GENERATOR PUTTERS)

25:00.440 --> 25:02.440
(MOTOR CHUGS SOFTLY)

25:07.360 --> 25:09.400
Hi, Dad.
DAVID: Hey.

25:09.400 --> 25:13.280
All good?
(LAUGHS) Yep, I'm fine. I'm fine.

25:13.280 --> 25:17.160
How are you? What are you doing?
Making my meatloaf, your favourite.

25:17.160 --> 25:19.760
Ohh!
There's enough for an army.

25:19.760 --> 25:23.320
Bring Mott.
He'll love that.

25:23.320 --> 25:25.320
You OK?

25:27.120 --> 25:28.760
Yeah. Yeah.

25:30.320 --> 25:33.760
Yeah, I'm-I'm fine.
I'm just...tired.

25:36.760 --> 25:38.800
I can't wait to see you.

25:40.320 --> 25:43.440
I love you.
I love you too.

25:43.440 --> 25:45.240
Hey, Ruth!

25:45.240 --> 25:48.240
Those Queenslanders, the ones
that abandoned you, they're here.

25:48.240 --> 25:49.720
Bullshit.

25:55.520 --> 25:58.480
Where the fuck were you last night?!
Sorry?

25:58.480 --> 26:01.320
Blue Wren Road, your truck was
called to help us, and then what?

26:01.320 --> 26:04.600
Hey, easy, what's going on?
We had another priority call.

26:05.600 --> 26:07.680
You got out! Shit, that's awesome.

26:07.680 --> 26:09.560
Awesome?!
Ruth, just...

26:09.560 --> 26:12.200
We...we don't decide
what jobs to go to.

26:12.200 --> 26:14.760
We were this close,
this fucking close.

26:14.760 --> 26:16.600
Nearly didn't make it.
Hey, just back off.

26:16.600 --> 26:18.840
OK, if you made it out,
then you should've reported it.

26:18.840 --> 26:20.760
It's not her fault.
OK, whose fault is it?

26:20.760 --> 26:22.560
Who is running this show?!
Just stop it, Ruth!

26:22.560 --> 26:24.800
They're just kids!
Fuck off, Nawra!

26:26.280 --> 26:28.160
Fuck off!

26:33.040 --> 26:35.800
I'm really sorry. I'm so sorry.

26:37.080 --> 26:38.520
Tash...

26:39.760 --> 26:42.720
Tash, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
(SOBS)

26:47.400 --> 26:48.400
Hey.

26:48.400 --> 26:51.160
Ohhh.
Just don't take it personally, yeah?

26:53.400 --> 26:55.200
How do I not?

27:03.560 --> 27:05.840
You leaving?
Yeah.

27:05.840 --> 27:08.480
Yeah, heard on your scanner
the coast road's clear

27:08.480 --> 27:10.320
so we're making a run
for the evacuation centre.

27:10.320 --> 27:13.680
You got a spare seat in your car?
Oh, yeah, just the one.

27:13.680 --> 27:15.960
Be a bit squishy, but.
It's not for me.

27:20.960 --> 27:22.800
(ENGINE RUMBLES)

27:24.920 --> 27:28.320
(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ON RADIO)

27:33.880 --> 27:38.320
Dumont ICC Operations
from Strike Team QFB 04.

27:38.320 --> 27:40.640
KIP: Come in, Strike Team QFB 04.

27:40.640 --> 27:43.560
Returning to station
to be relieved for changeover.

27:43.560 --> 27:44.920
Copy that.

27:46.480 --> 27:50.240
That Blue Wren priority call,
the residents made it out.

27:50.240 --> 27:53.040
They were sheltering in a business
in town with a few others.

27:58.520 --> 28:00.680
What's their condition?

28:00.680 --> 28:02.200
Pissed as hell.

28:05.280 --> 28:07.280
(CHUCKLES)

28:08.480 --> 28:11.120
Yep, fair enough. Over.

28:12.760 --> 28:14.440
That's good news.

28:16.280 --> 28:18.080
Still mad at you.

28:18.080 --> 28:19.960
Not as mad, though.

28:25.400 --> 28:28.360
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

28:32.280 --> 28:33.880
(COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYS)
Oh, there we go.

28:33.880 --> 28:36.280
No, can't hear the radio.
(MUSIC STOPS)

28:36.280 --> 28:38.320
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

28:38.320 --> 28:39.880
One song.

28:39.880 --> 28:41.640
('SOMEBODY SPECIAL'
BY DONNA FARGO PLAYS)

28:41.640 --> 28:43.840
# You can sing me anytime... #
Oh, Donna!

28:43.840 --> 28:47.800
You love Donna. Come on - Donna.
You and Donna go way back! (LAUGHS)

28:47.800 --> 28:50.080
(SINGS ALONG TO RADIO)
# God blessed me good with you

28:50.080 --> 28:52.760
# You're the reason I keep trying

28:52.760 --> 28:55.200
# When I give up like I do

28:55.200 --> 28:57.720
# You're the one that makes me happy

28:57.720 --> 29:00.000
# And you know just because of you

29:00.000 --> 29:03.840
# Sometimes
I even feel like I'm... #

29:03.840 --> 29:06.240
Come on, next line, next one, ready?
I don't know the lyrics.

29:06.240 --> 29:08.360
Come on. You gotta know the lyrics.
No.

29:08.360 --> 29:11.280
# So when you tell me
that you're lonely

29:11.280 --> 29:13.200
# And you think that
I don't care... #

29:13.200 --> 29:14.800
(LAUGHS) I got it. OK, OK, OK.

29:14.800 --> 29:17.000
(SINGS ALONG)
# I may not know how to show you

29:17.000 --> 29:18.920
# But I promise to be there

29:18.920 --> 29:21.720
# For as long as you can love me... #
There it is!

29:21.720 --> 29:24.120
# And want me to love you... #
(LAUGHS) There it is.

29:24.120 --> 29:27.640
# That's the reason
for everything I do... #

29:27.640 --> 29:29.280
That's right. See? Yeah, come on.

29:29.280 --> 29:31.960
(SINGS ALONG)
# You're my somebody special

29:31.960 --> 29:34.480
# God blessed me good with you

29:34.480 --> 29:36.960
(SINGS ALONG)
# You're the reason I keep trying

29:36.960 --> 29:39.560
# When I give up like I do

29:39.560 --> 29:41.760
# You're the one that makes me happy

29:41.760 --> 29:44.440
# And you know just because of you

29:44.440 --> 29:47.960
# Sometimes I even feel like I'm

29:47.960 --> 29:52.400
# Somebody special too. #

30:14.080 --> 30:15.080
You packing?

30:17.040 --> 30:19.400
That one's mine.

30:21.720 --> 30:23.480
You wanted to go.

30:23.480 --> 30:27.680
No, you decided that,
like you decide everything.

30:29.600 --> 30:31.400
I loved you.

30:33.360 --> 30:37.120
I still love you...
because I'm an idiot.

30:39.000 --> 30:41.280
But don't worry, I'll get over it.

30:45.360 --> 30:47.880
(SNIFFS)

30:47.880 --> 30:50.520
(VEHICLE APPROACHES)

30:57.320 --> 30:59.720
(GASPS) Leo!

30:59.720 --> 31:02.360
Oh, God, you're alright. Oh!

31:02.360 --> 31:03.520
(LEO LAUGHS)

31:03.520 --> 31:07.320
Oh, we thought...
Oh, you're alright!

31:08.720 --> 31:12.640
Oh, you're alright.
We... Oh, we thought that...

31:14.440 --> 31:17.120
Oh, God, it's good to see you!

31:17.120 --> 31:19.280
(SHAKILY) Where's Maria?

31:20.920 --> 31:22.600
Maria.

31:23.800 --> 31:25.120
Maria!

31:25.120 --> 31:28.800
Leo! (LAUGHS) Leo! Leo!

31:32.320 --> 31:36.160
Oh, you stupid, stupid man.
I was so worried about you!

31:36.160 --> 31:38.760
I dropped the bloody phone
in the mud, I couldn't call you.

31:38.760 --> 31:41.600
We found him when we went up
to try and save their place.

31:41.600 --> 31:44.280
Yeah, he and the poddy
were up to their necks in mud.

31:44.280 --> 31:48.600
Daisy's new calf got stuck. I had
to hold his head above the water.

31:48.600 --> 31:52.080
Can you imagine being so stupid
that you drown in a fire?

31:52.080 --> 31:54.480
MARIA: Is he alright?
Yeah.

32:04.520 --> 32:07.560
Ah, we've gotta get him to hospital,
get him checked out.

32:07.560 --> 32:10.800
Oh, yeah,
I've only got the one seat spare.

32:10.800 --> 32:12.320
He can take my space.

32:12.320 --> 32:14.760
I'm not going anywhere
without this old thing.

32:14.760 --> 32:16.840
Will you...
Will you stop fussing at me?!

32:16.840 --> 32:18.560
(LEO AND MARIA LAUGH)

32:18.560 --> 32:22.120
MACCA: Alright, well, looks like
the seat's yours again, Nawra.

32:22.120 --> 32:24.440
Come on, let's go. Let's go.

32:29.360 --> 32:32.080
I can't take Joey to the city.

32:34.000 --> 32:36.680
I can handle microwaving a bottle.

32:45.840 --> 32:48.920
OK, Macca, stick to the main roads.

32:48.920 --> 32:51.840
Keep the radio on at all times.

32:51.840 --> 32:53.920
And for God's sake, just be...

32:54.920 --> 32:56.720
..just be careful, son.

32:58.160 --> 32:59.800
Good luck.

33:07.640 --> 33:10.520
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

33:22.080 --> 33:24.360
No. Wait!

33:24.360 --> 33:26.400
Wait! Wait!
Stop.

33:26.400 --> 33:28.360
Macca, Macca, stop, stop.
What now?

33:32.200 --> 33:35.080
Um... (BREATHES HEAVILY)

33:35.080 --> 33:36.760
Where's that bottle again?

33:38.960 --> 33:40.520
It's in the bag.

33:40.520 --> 33:42.400
Alright.
Gotta get moving, Ruth.

33:42.400 --> 33:44.680
Yeah. Um...

33:46.240 --> 33:49.000
Um, how much of the formula?

33:52.000 --> 33:56.720
A teaspoon in 100 mils.
OK, good, I always forget that.

33:56.720 --> 33:58.760
Ruth, come on.

33:58.760 --> 34:01.560
Can you just wait a... I'm...

34:01.560 --> 34:03.840
(SIGHS)

34:05.840 --> 34:08.240
I'm really hopeless
with a lot of stuff.

34:08.240 --> 34:10.120
Yeah, you are.

34:11.120 --> 34:13.640
Come with us, stay here,
I don't really care,

34:13.640 --> 34:15.600
just...I've gotta drive.

34:19.040 --> 34:20.840
I don't want you to go.

34:24.240 --> 34:27.480
OK. Will you please stay, Nawra?

34:29.720 --> 34:31.200
Please?

34:38.200 --> 34:41.120
(SEATBELT BUCKLE CLICKS)

34:51.680 --> 34:53.800
(HORN BEEPS)

35:00.360 --> 35:02.440
(WINDMILL SQUEAKS)

35:07.760 --> 35:09.920
Didn't we meet sitting in a gutter?

35:09.920 --> 35:12.680
Yeah, outside the Prince.
Mmm.

35:12.680 --> 35:15.440
(LAUGHS) Classy from the start, huh?

35:15.440 --> 35:17.960
Yeah, you know it.
Mmm.

35:17.960 --> 35:19.560
(LAUGHS)

35:23.640 --> 35:26.640
So, uh, you wanna
come back to mine?

35:26.640 --> 35:28.600
Mmmm. (LAUGHS)

35:30.640 --> 35:34.200
I mean, the place is a bit
of a fixer-upper, but...

35:37.440 --> 35:39.360
..apparently so am I.

35:42.160 --> 35:44.840
Good bones, though.
Yeah?

35:44.840 --> 35:47.400
Yeah, I think we can
make something of it.

35:47.400 --> 35:50.160
You do?
Yeah, I do.

35:58.560 --> 35:59.920
Shit.

36:00.960 --> 36:02.600
Oh, fuck.

36:02.600 --> 36:04.120
Greg!

36:10.680 --> 36:14.360
Ah, wind change, south-west,
turning towards Curran.

36:14.360 --> 36:17.360
(LEAVES RUSTLE LOUDLY,
HEAVY WIND BLOWS)

36:25.160 --> 36:29.800
(CREAKING THEN THUDDING)
Whoa, where did that come from?

36:29.800 --> 36:31.400
That's weird.

36:31.400 --> 36:34.040
(LEAVES RUSTLE LOUDLY)

36:40.280 --> 36:42.960
(LEAVES RUSTLE LOUDLY)

36:45.960 --> 36:48.960
(WINDMILL SQUEAKS)
(FOREBODING MUSIC BUILDS)

36:55.120 --> 36:57.880
(WIND BLOWS LOUDLY)

37:02.520 --> 37:04.640
Fuck me, not again.

37:06.240 --> 37:09.760
Alright, we have a Red Flag Warning,
please acknowledge.

37:09.760 --> 37:14.640
Uh, wind change, south-west, 80.
Curran township under direct attack.

37:14.640 --> 37:17.960
Inform and acknowledge.
Pull whatever you can from Borriga!

37:17.960 --> 37:19.480
Pull 'em from anywhere you can!

37:19.480 --> 37:21.080
MAN ON RADIO:
Tillerton sector commander,

37:21.080 --> 37:23.080
all appliances acknowledge Red Flag.

37:23.080 --> 37:26.200
DELL: Copy that, Tillerton,
leave Borriga firegrounds.

37:26.200 --> 37:30.240
Set up Curran exit control south
of the bridge. Curran under attack.

37:30.240 --> 37:33.400
It'll be too late by the time they
get down there. We're the closest.

37:33.400 --> 37:36.400
No! Come on,
we're on changeover, Tash.

37:36.400 --> 37:38.400
But all those people in town.

37:38.400 --> 37:40.480
You wanna let scary lady
have another go at you?

37:40.480 --> 37:42.600
Mott!
No!

37:42.600 --> 37:45.840
Curran will hold until
the other crews get there, OK?

37:45.840 --> 37:48.840
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

37:50.120 --> 37:52.280
Mott...

37:55.120 --> 37:57.680
Pleeeeease?

38:05.320 --> 38:07.520
Fine.
(LAUGHS)

38:12.600 --> 38:17.600
Dumont ICC Operations
from Strike Team QFB 04,

38:17.600 --> 38:20.480
we're heading back to Curran, we'll
set up control and send word back.

38:20.480 --> 38:26.160
Copy that. And, hey, thank you.
I owe you a beer when this is over.

38:26.160 --> 38:29.080
Yeah, make it a keg.
Copy that.

38:31.440 --> 38:34.320
(WIND RUMBLES)

38:37.080 --> 38:40.080
(LEAVES RUSTLE LOUDLY)

38:41.480 --> 38:43.880
Get inside! Get inside!

38:43.880 --> 38:46.520
We're gonna start wetting down!

38:51.640 --> 38:53.680
KIP ON RADIO: Strike Team QFB 04...

38:53.680 --> 38:57.120
They're sending trucks.
..about 10 minutes away from Curran.

38:57.120 --> 38:58.800
Report crews nearby.

38:58.800 --> 39:02.160
That's the Queenslanders
who were here, the young ones.

39:03.160 --> 39:05.080
Might as well have dessert first.

39:08.680 --> 39:10.720
Now, I know you and I haven't

39:10.720 --> 39:13.640
exactly seen eye to eye
politically always,

39:13.640 --> 39:16.200
but I like strawberry,
you like choc mint.

39:16.200 --> 39:18.840
No-one likes choc mint, Rollo.

39:18.840 --> 39:21.160
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

39:24.400 --> 39:28.160
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

39:28.160 --> 39:30.040
(WIND BLOWS LOUDLY)

39:34.320 --> 39:36.480
(FOREBODING MUSIC BUILDS)

39:36.480 --> 39:38.720
(THUDDING)

39:38.720 --> 39:40.160
(LEAVES RUSTLE LOUDLY)

39:46.640 --> 39:51.440
KIP: ICC Operations to
Strike Team QFB 04, please report.

39:51.440 --> 39:53.920
Strike Team QFB 04...

39:55.720 --> 39:58.720
(CLANKING AND RUMBLING)

39:58.720 --> 40:00.080
Shit!

40:01.920 --> 40:03.880
(RATTLING)

40:06.040 --> 40:08.440
(WHOOSHING)
Holy shit!

40:10.760 --> 40:13.160
(METAL CRUNCHING AND CLANKING)

40:13.160 --> 40:14.320
(THUD!)
Oh!

40:20.960 --> 40:23.960
(CRASH NOISE VANISHES)
(YELLS AND GASPS)

40:27.440 --> 40:29.520
(RUMBLING)

40:32.080 --> 40:33.600
(EXHALES)

40:33.600 --> 40:35.600
(LOUD CRASHING)
(SCREAMS)

40:41.160 --> 40:42.880
(SOMBRE MUSIC)

40:48.360 --> 40:50.000
(MOTT GROANS)

40:50.000 --> 40:52.840
KIP: Strike Team QFB 04
from Dumont ICC Operations.

40:52.840 --> 40:55.080
I didn't quite catch that last bit.
Could you please repeat?

40:55.080 --> 40:57.760
(GRUNTS) Tash?

40:59.360 --> 41:02.000
Queensland, repeat?
Tash?

41:04.160 --> 41:05.880
(GROANS)
Queensland?

41:05.880 --> 41:08.160
(GASPS AND GRUNTS)

41:15.440 --> 41:17.600
Come in, Queensland Strike Team.
Tash?

41:17.600 --> 41:20.160
(UNSETTLING MUSIC BUILDS)

41:25.960 --> 41:28.240
(GROANS)

41:33.080 --> 41:35.880
Tash? (GRUNTS) Tash?

41:41.200 --> 41:43.000
I've lost the strike team.

41:46.560 --> 41:49.160
I've got you. I've got you.

41:49.160 --> 41:50.640
OK. OK.

41:52.080 --> 41:53.560
(GROANS)

41:54.880 --> 41:57.040
(GROANS LOUDLY)

42:00.480 --> 42:01.960
(MOTT PANTS)

42:03.480 --> 42:05.600
Tash?

42:05.600 --> 42:07.360
Tash?!

42:07.360 --> 42:09.160
Tash?

42:09.160 --> 42:12.160
Come on. Come on. Hey.

42:12.160 --> 42:15.200
Hey. Look at me. Look at me.

42:15.200 --> 42:16.880
(GROANS SOFTLY)

42:16.880 --> 42:18.360
(WHISPERS) Hey.

42:21.000 --> 42:23.520
I can't feel my... (GASPS SHARPLY)

42:23.520 --> 42:25.080
Tash, it's alright. It's alright.
(GROANS)

42:25.080 --> 42:27.280
Don't move, don't move, don't move.
I can't move my...

42:27.280 --> 42:28.520
(GROANS)

42:28.520 --> 42:31.320
I'm gonna radio them
for help, OK? Yeah?

42:33.240 --> 42:35.160
(WHISPERS) Thanks.

42:35.160 --> 42:37.480
(BREATHES RAPIDLY) Tash?

42:37.480 --> 42:39.680
Tash, stay awake.

42:39.680 --> 42:42.040
Tash, stay with me.

42:42.040 --> 42:43.920
Tash!

42:45.520 --> 42:47.720
(WHISPERS) Oh, shit.

42:50.600 --> 42:53.440
MOTT: Come in, Dumont ICC...
(COUGHS AND GROANS)

42:53.440 --> 42:56.920
(GROANS) Fuck! Ahhh! Emergency.

42:56.920 --> 43:00.080
The truck slipped, impact,
the crew leader...

43:01.080 --> 43:04.600
Tash is hurt real bad and
we need help, OK?! We need help!

43:04.600 --> 43:06.000
DELL: Keep him calm.
OK.

43:06.000 --> 43:07.160
Ask if she's breathing.
Alright.

43:07.160 --> 43:09.720
Hello. Ambulance, please.

43:09.720 --> 43:12.080
Is she breathing?
Ah, I don't know. I think so.

43:12.080 --> 43:14.320
Hang on. (GROANS)

43:14.320 --> 43:16.120
Ah, w-what's your location?

43:19.280 --> 43:20.600
I don't know.

43:20.600 --> 43:24.880
Just...just a road...road name, an
intersection, a landmark, anything.

43:24.880 --> 43:27.680
Um, we crossed a bridge
not too long ago.

43:27.680 --> 43:29.200
DELL: I know that spot.

43:29.200 --> 43:30.920
She's not breathing.

43:32.080 --> 43:35.120
Anderson's Road,
about 2km north of the highway.

43:35.120 --> 43:36.600
Ambos on their way.

43:36.600 --> 43:38.280
You're gonna have to give her CPR.

43:38.280 --> 43:40.560
I can talk you through it
until the ambos get there.

43:41.560 --> 43:44.480
OK, so what you need to do
is...is push down on the chest hard,

43:44.480 --> 43:46.560
do 30 compressions,
then two breaths.

43:46.560 --> 43:47.560
MOTT: OK.

43:47.560 --> 43:50.080
How about you count aloud
so I can count with you, mate?

43:50.080 --> 43:52.960
OK. 30...30 compressions.

43:52.960 --> 43:56.360
One, two, three, four,

43:56.360 --> 44:00.520
five, six, seven, eight, nine...

44:00.520 --> 44:03.520
KIP: 10, 11, 12,

44:03.520 --> 44:05.760
13, 14,

44:05.760 --> 44:10.200
15, 16, 17, 18, 19...

44:10.200 --> 44:12.840
20, 21, 22...
20, 21, 22, 23,

44:12.840 --> 44:17.320
24, 25, 26, 27, 28,

44:17.320 --> 44:19.680
29, 30.

44:21.880 --> 44:23.240
Now go for another round.

44:23.240 --> 44:24.600
Compressions, OK? Let's go.

44:24.600 --> 44:27.320
Come on, Tash, one, two...
One, two...

44:27.320 --> 44:28.920
(COUNTING FADES) ..three, four,

44:28.920 --> 44:31.400
five, six, seven...

44:31.400 --> 44:34.680
(UNSETTLING MUSIC)

44:37.360 --> 44:40.480
(GRUNTS)

44:45.240 --> 44:47.720
(SOBS)

44:49.200 --> 44:51.040
(WEEPS) Elev...

44:52.800 --> 44:55.800
(SOBS LOUDLY)

45:07.000 --> 45:09.320
(GULPS THEN EXHALES HARD)

45:10.800 --> 45:12.960
Tash? (SNIFFS)

45:12.960 --> 45:15.120
(BRIGHTLY) Hey? Hey, Tash.

45:15.120 --> 45:18.360
(VOICE BREAKS)
Please...please breathe.

45:20.480 --> 45:21.960
Please.

45:23.320 --> 45:25.880
(SHAKILY) Please breathe.

45:32.000 --> 45:35.000
(TAKES GULPING BREATHS)

45:41.600 --> 45:43.720
It's OK, I got you.

45:45.160 --> 45:47.280
(SNIFFS) I got you.

45:49.960 --> 45:52.200
(GASPS SHAKILY)

45:56.240 --> 45:58.080
(SNIFFS)

46:02.720 --> 46:04.720
(WHISPERS) I got you.

46:27.080 --> 46:30.080
(DISTANT SIREN GROWS LOUDER)

46:50.800 --> 46:52.680
MAN ON RADIO:
Curran Sector Command,

46:52.680 --> 46:55.560
Tanker 1 approaching Curran,
ETA five minutes.

46:55.560 --> 46:57.520
Copy that, Curran.

46:57.520 --> 46:59.720
Set up control and send word back.

47:01.600 --> 47:03.720
Uh, Tillerton Command,
please report location.

47:03.720 --> 47:06.240
DELL: Copy that.
Dumont ICC Operations.

47:06.240 --> 47:09.880
(SOMBRE MUSIC)

47:11.640 --> 47:14.320
(BIRD CHIRPS AND TRILLS)

47:20.480 --> 47:22.640
(BIRDS TWITTER)

47:39.800 --> 47:43.360
REPORTER: It was a case of
every man and woman for themselves

47:43.360 --> 47:46.160
when a group in the small community
of Curran

47:46.160 --> 47:49.240
managed to survive by
sheltering in a local shop,

47:49.240 --> 47:53.320
protected by a DIY firefighting unit
until help arrived.

47:53.320 --> 47:56.000
There's been some
international criticism

47:56.000 --> 47:58.440
of Australia's response
to the fires.

47:58.440 --> 48:00.760
What do you say to that?
ROLLO: Yeah.

48:00.760 --> 48:03.600
Well, no-one would've known the
scale these fires were gonna reach.

48:03.600 --> 48:06.240
Oh, they knew, Rollo!
MAN: Look around you, mate!

48:06.240 --> 48:08.320
Is there something
you'd like to say?

48:08.320 --> 48:10.560
It's not the time
for politics, Ruth.

48:11.840 --> 48:13.320
You...

48:14.760 --> 48:17.000
People here are doing
everything they can.

48:17.000 --> 48:19.720
They're fighting.

48:19.720 --> 48:23.480
But that's not enough, the...
This is too big.

48:23.480 --> 48:25.960
Our home burned down around us.

48:25.960 --> 48:28.040
We didn't think that
we were gonna get out.

48:28.040 --> 48:31.400
NAWRA: Our neighbours, our friends,
they've got NOTHING left.

48:31.400 --> 48:33.000
They've got nowhere to go.

48:33.000 --> 48:36.080
It's the same with the animals,
all the beautiful wild animals.

48:36.080 --> 48:39.080
Their...their habitat
is completely destroyed.

48:39.080 --> 48:42.520
And people are dying,
like really young people,

48:42.520 --> 48:45.160
before they've even had a life.

48:45.160 --> 48:47.200
I... Wh...
Yeah.

48:47.200 --> 48:49.480
I mean, how bad does it have to get

48:49.480 --> 48:52.200
before somebody
actually does something?!

48:52.200 --> 48:55.720
Isn't this enough?! Isn't it?!

48:58.400 --> 49:00.400
(LEAVES RUSTLE SOFTLY)

49:05.000 --> 49:08.000
(INTENSE MUSIC)

49:17.560 --> 49:19.440
NEWSREADER: This is
an emergency warning.

49:19.440 --> 49:21.800
There is a bushfire to the west
that is out of control.

49:21.800 --> 49:24.000
Move to the beach or the wharf!

49:24.000 --> 49:25.680
Baba! Mama!

49:25.680 --> 49:28.440
I lost my parents
and now I can't find them.

49:28.440 --> 49:30.480
I've gotta protect my place.
I can't stay with her.

49:30.480 --> 49:32.800
We need to get a message out.
You want me to help you?

49:34.880 --> 49:38.440
A large cloud formed by the fire
is cutting out the light.

49:38.440 --> 49:41.920
Adut! Come on!
It's safer in the water.

49:41.920 --> 49:44.520
The fire's hitting houses
on the outskirts of town.

49:45.720 --> 49:47.680
(HELICOPTER CLATTERS)

49:47.680 --> 49:49.360
I can't look after you, kid!

49:49.360 --> 49:51.720
MAN: The fire was right at the back.
We're gonna help you.

49:51.720 --> 49:54.800
Hold on, everyone, and good luck.

